06:15.700 --> 06:18.200
Besides, isn't today
closing arguments?

06:18.200 --> 06:20.200
It's not like I'm
actually in the courtroom.

06:20.400 --> 06:22.200
Devalos just likes to have me
around the office,

06:22.200 --> 06:25.000
just hanging around
in case he needs something.

06:25.700 --> 06:28.000
Trust me, he won't
even notice if I'm not there.

06:28.000 --> 06:28.900
It's okay.

06:29.500 --> 06:30.900
Be there. I'll be fine.

06:31.200 --> 06:33.400
DEVALOS:
 <i>What does</i>
 <i>"circumstantial" mean?</i>

06:34.800 --> 06:38.800
The defense will try to attack the people's case
as "circumstantial."

06:38.800 --> 06:41.400
They want you to assume

06:41.400 --> 06:44.700
that "circumstantial" and "not
guilty" are one and the same.

06:44.700 --> 06:46.400
They are not. You know this.

06:47.500 --> 06:49.600
Your common sense
will tell you this--

06:49.600 --> 06:53.100
your common sense
in combination with the testimony you've
heard in this courtroom.

06:53.100 --> 06:55.400
So let's review that testimony.

06:55.900 --> 06:58.300
You've heard
from Walter Paxton's bookies

06:58.300 --> 06:58.900
and business associates.

06:58.900 --> 07:01.600
They've testified to his lies,

07:02.000 --> 07:04.100
his history
of stealing from his wife

07:04.100 --> 07:06.400
and his escalating
gambling debts.

07:06.400 --> 07:08.800
You've heard from Natalie
Paxton's accountants,

07:08.800 --> 07:11.400
how they had recently
informed Mr. Paxton

07:11.400 --> 07:13.300
that he was about to be cut off.

07:14.100 --> 07:16.200
You've heard from a number of
matrimonial 

07:16.200 --> 07:19.200
and family attorneys testifying
to the iron-clad nature

07:19.200 --> 07:22.800
of Walter and his late wife's
prenuptial agreement,

07:22.800 --> 07:24.600
how anything other
than his wife's death

07:24.600 --> 07:28.100
would leave him broke and
in debt to violent criminals.

07:28.300 --> 07:30.500
And you've heard
a proprietor of a knife shop say

07:30.500 --> 07:32.500
that the defendant
purchased a blade

07:32.500 --> 07:35.500
that matches the incisions
on Natalie Paxton's body--

07:35.500 --> 07:41.100
a knife that he cannot or
will not produce for this court.

07:42.600 --> 07:44.300
You've heard about
the night of the killing.

07:45.000 --> 07:46.700
The screaming fight
in the hotel room.

07:46.700 --> 07:50.000
The defendant seen leaving
the lobby carrying a satchel.

07:50.600 --> 07:54.800
The three subsequent hours for which the defendant
cannot account,

07:54.800 --> 07:58.200
hours spent, he claims,
driving the streets in anger.

07:59.100 --> 08:01.100
And it was during those hours,

08:01.100 --> 08:03.100
that the defendant,
Walter Paxton,

08:03.100 --> 08:06.100
would have you believe
that someone else

08:06.700 --> 08:10.700
entered his hotel room,
someone else using Walter Paxton's key card,

08:11.400 --> 08:15.100
Someone else with a knife
exactly like Walter Paxton's.

08:15.300 --> 08:16.400
And once inside,

08:16.400 --> 08:18.500
what did this someone else do?

08:18.800 --> 08:22.200
Why, he decapitated Walter's
Paxton's wife, of course,

08:22.200 --> 08:24.600
and kept her head as a souvenir!

08:26.700 --> 08:28.100
JUDGE:
Please, folks.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.400
So what do we think?

08:30.500 --> 08:32.000
I'd rather have a
knife or some DNA

08:32.000 --> 08:33.700
or a fingerprint,
but failing that...

08:33.700 --> 08:36.299
you were pretty
damn magnificent.

08:36.500 --> 08:38.299
Ah. Terrific.

08:39.500 --> 08:40.200
No, I'm here.

08:40.200 --> 08:41.100
I'm not going anywhere.

08:41.100 --> 08:43.400
Maybe just grab
a sandwich or something.

08:44.200 --> 08:45.000
Okay.

08:45.000 --> 08:46.400
See you then.

08:48.600 --> 08:49.400
Can I help you?

08:49.400 --> 08:51.400
Yeah, I, um, I'm,
so sorry to bother you.

08:51.400 --> 08:54.900
Do you happen to own a beige-colored
Volvo station wagon?

08:55.000 --> 08:58.200
Parked on the ground floor of
the municipal garage out here?

08:58.800 --> 08:59.700
WOMAN:
 <i>I feel terrible.</i>

